news.title: Credai meets Goa revenue minister, seeks ease of doing business
news.para: Credai Goa president Nilesh Salkar said the meeting was convened with the aim to “talk about the issues and concerns” that Goa’s builders have.

news.title: DDA issues notice to set up consortium for three sectors under land pooling
news.para: The DDA has also issued a public notice to all the land owners to register objections with reference to their list of pooled lands under the policy.

news.title: Mumbai: 1979 building shown as garden space in development plans, society pays heavily for BMC error
news.para: It was only around 2006-07 that the residents of Arun Cooperative Housing Society, most of them senior citizens, learnt of it when they wanted to go in for redevelopment.

news.title: Regulatory framework, robust returns set to prompt Indian REITs next growth phase
news.para: The country’s maiden REIT listed on bourses over three years ago on April 1, 2019 with Blackstone Group and Embassy Group taking their joint office assets platform Embassy Office Parks public.

news.title: DLF's sales bookings jumps over two-fold to Rs 7,273 crore during FY22
news.para: The company said this has been its strongest performance in the last 10 years. Its super luxury project 'The Camellias' continues to evince strong customer interest and delivered healthy sales bookings of Rs 2,550 crore during the last fiscal.

news.title: Preeti Chandra is flight risk, mastermind of conspiracy in passing info inside Tihar: ED to SC
news.para: Additional Solicitor General Madhavi Divan, appearing for ED, said that the application has been filed by Preeti at the time when the Supreme Court is on the cusp of going into summer vacation and she poses an enormous flight risk.

news.title: JK Lakshmi Cement's profit rises 18.3% to Rs 188.36 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: Its revenue from operations was up 12.32 per cent at Rs 1,599.83 crore during the quarter under review as against Rs 1,424.32 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Noida: Buyers in a fix as 11 illegal flats in Antriksh Golf View 1 society sealed
news.para: On Tuesday, 11 of the 22 flats were sealed by the Authority. This was after complaints of illegal construction in the stilt parking area of the society were found to be true.

news.title: DTCP blacklists Mahira Buildtech & Czar Buildwell for forgery
news.para: In his order issued on Tuesday evening, DTCP director KM Pandurang said these two developers submitted “fabricated bank guarantees” and also “forged signatures of bank officials” while procuring the licences for their projects.

news.title: Ascendas India Trust to acquire first industrial property in Chennai for Rs 212 crore
news.para: This is pursuant to the forward purchase arrangement with the shareholders of Chengalpattu Logistics Parks, as announced on 5 March 2021.

news.title: Settlement proposal with bank submitted in NCLAT, erstwhile management of Supertech to SC
news.para: The bench said, "You have placed it. They (NCLAT) will consider it. We should not be issuing any such direction for consideration. It is not appropriate for us to direct them".

news.title: Lender asks Supertech to deposit Rs 75 crore as upfront payment for considering OTS
news.para: The realty firm had offered to make an upfront payment of Rs 10 crore with 10 crore on acceptance of OTS, however, the public sector lender asked to deposit Rs 75 crore as a condition to consider for settlement.

news.title: BHIVE Fund to raise Rs 400 crore to invest in commercial office projects
news.para: BHIVE, the parent company, will be the sponsor of the fund and will invest in office properties with occupancy certificates ranging between 15,000 sq. ft. and 50,000 sq. ft. across Bangalore.

news.title: Brookfield India REIT's net profit registers 63.61% growth in Q4 FY22
news.para: The company's total consolidated income stood at Rs 2,613.91 millions in Q4 FY22, a growth of 92 per cent from Rs 1,361.07 millions it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Bajaj Electricals' net profit down 29% at Rs 39 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: However, total revenue from operations was up 6.02 per cent at Rs 1,334.32 crore during the quarter under review as against Rs 1,258.47 crore in the year-ago period.
